description: A LINQ to MDX Psued-O-RM for Microsoft SQL Server Analysis Services
releaseNotes:
Finally, a way to query a Microsoft SQL Server Analysis Database with LINQ and type safe objects! 

Beta version - Comes without any warranties.  Please contact me via the "Contact Owners" link for any questions, comments, bugs, or features you think should be included. Make sure to read the "Documentation" text file that is included with the package. 

Changes: 
-Added a type of implementation to include a sub cube using PAS syntax.

-Fixed a further issue with sub cubes and PAS syntax that prevented it from querying.

-Update the documentation file.  It was horribly out of date.

-Added ability to add and remove objects in a PAS query more easily.

-Added functionality in the translator to automatically add the member group extension on an attribute, i.e.  cube.Sales.StoreID will now translate to [Sales].[Store ID].[Store ID].

Coming Changes:
-Fixing a bug with creating query scoped calculated members or sets in a cube's partial class, throwing the exception saying something similar to "Calculated members or set must use the WithSet attribute or WithMember attribute".

-Changing the generator to only generate each dimension once, and sharing them among their respective cube classes.
summary: A LINQ to MDX Psued-O-RM for Microsoft SQL Server Analysis Services
